Some capillaries on anterior rows with distinct transverse barring pattern, composed of partitions and chambers in shafts, giving chaetae a cracked appearance; reticulations sometimes interspersed with dense groups of granules. Pygidium with midventral flap or flange and either one (

Dispio lenislamellata


sp. nov.

) or two pairs of long cirri (

D. anauncinata


sp. nov.

) or absent (

D. magnus

), or pygidium reduced with small papillae on ventral surface (

D. latilamella

).
